Here's an updated JUnit5 test case that should work:

@Test
public void testInvalidCsv() {
    // Set up your test environment, such as setting filePath
    String testFilePath = "/path/to/invalid/file";
    CsvReader reader = new CsvReader();

    // Call the readCsv() method and assert that it throws an IOException
    Exception exception = assertThrows(IOException.class, () -> {
        reader.readCsv(testFilePath);
    });

    // Assert that the exception message contains "Invalid CSV file"
    assertTrue(exception.getMessage().contains("Invalid CSV file"));
}

In this updated test case, we create a new instance of the CsvReader class and set the filePath to point to an invalid file. We then call the readCsv() method and assert that it throws an IOException. Finally, we assert that the exception message contains the expected error message.